TUF Ops — Master Version Map
North Star
TUF Ops is not a CRM.
It is a Revenue Operating System built to help TUF:
	•	identify opportunities
	•	move them through a disciplined sales process
	•	manage people and territories
	•	convert deals into revenue
	•	hand off won business into operations cleanly
	•	scale leadership visibility without losing control
That means the roadmap has to build in this order:
	1	Product surface
	2	Record quality
	3	Workflow discipline
	4	People and territory management
	5	Revenue capture
	6	Operational handoff
	7	Enterprise hardening

Non-Negotiable Product Principles
These should govern every version.
1. Action over analytics
The system should always answer:
What should happen next?
Not just show data.
2. One source of truth
Organizations, opportunities, owners, stages, and handoffs must be standardized.
3. Modular growth
Every major capability should be a layer:
	•	dashboard
	•	records
	•	workflow
	•	people
	•	finance
	•	ops
4. State discipline
This system will only scale if records can exist in clean, predictable states.
5. Leadership visibility without clutter
Reps need focus. Directors need oversight. Admins need control.

System Capabilities Required by Launch
By launch, TUF Ops should be able to handle:
Users
	•	admin
	•	national director
	•	regional director
	•	territory manager
	•	sales rep
	•	ops user
	•	finance/admin support
Entities
	•	organizations
	•	opportunities
	•	users
	•	territories
	•	stages
	•	activities
	•	tasks / next steps
	•	mockups
	•	samples
	•	invoices
	•	handoffs
	•	orders
Core behaviors
	•	assign ownership
	•	track stage progression
	•	highlight stale deals
	•	show next actions
	•	route deals by territory/user
	•	show leadership dashboards
	•	trigger handoff when deal is won
	•	preserve history and accountability

